verbose_text: XREF_BIBR The brain level of quinolinic acid should also be measured to determine its change following alpha-lactalbumin ingestion and to establish whether the net effect of alpha-lactalbumin ingestion is ultimately to stimulate or to inhibit the action of N-methyl-d-aspartate receptors.
